main event: On April 6, 1960, unidentified aerial objects were observed in the sky over Guantanamo Bay, Cuba, and photographed by the crews of various US naval vessels.
interesting points: The objects were metallic, circular in shape, and approximately 30-40 feet in diameter,The objects were observed maneuvering at high speeds and making sharp turns,The sightings lasted for about 2 hours,No sound was heard from the objects during the observation,The photographs and documentation have been forwarded to Project Blue Book for further analysis.
witness description: crews of various US naval vessels
